CH. 22, §L praefectura annonae: this was the chief official position tenable by a Roman knight, next to that of ‘praefectus praetorio ’ and the ‘ praefectura Aegypti!

Faenio Rufo: this officer obtained a good reputation in this office, which led to his promotion to be ‘ praefectus praetorio' on Burrus’ death, (xiv 51, 5). He joined in the conspiracy of Piso, and suffered death (xv 50, 68).

Arruntius Stella is otherwise not known. There was a L. Arruntius Stella, cos. suff. under Trajan, and often mentioned as a poet by Marffial, who possibly was this' man's son.
